  "prompt": "What are the techniques/scripting languages used for real-time updating of webpage contents without refreshing the page?",
  "response": "There are several techniques and technologies used for real-time updating of webpage contents without refreshing the page:\n\n1. AJAX (Asynchronous JavaScript and XML)\n- Using XMLHttpRequest or Fetch API\n- Allows partial page updates\n- Makes asynchronous server requests\n- Lightweight and widely supported\n\nExample:\n```javascript\nfetch('/data')\n  .then(response => response.json())\n  .then(data => {\n    document.getElementById('content').innerHTML = data;\n  });\n```\n\n2. WebSockets\n- Full-duplex, real-time communication\n- Persistent connection between client and server\n- Low latency and efficient\n- Ideal for live updates and streaming\n\nExample:\n```javascript\nconst socket = new WebSocket('ws://example.com/socket');\nsocket.onmessage = (event) => {\n  updateContent(event.data);\n};\n```\n\n3. Server-Sent Events (SSE)\n- One",
